{STRUAN WOOD 790660 Long ago,before man came to live here there were{birch trees}growing on the slopes of An Teampan.This wood made up of hairy and silver birch was formed about 8,700 years ago after the last great Ice Age. A moth which is found nowhere else in Britain, lives in this birch wood. It does not have an English name, only a Latin one, because it is so rare. It is called{Ancylis Tineana.}The female is flightless and the species can only survive with continuous tree cover.
